+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Xjti9N5AyZZeeyyCaEMWRN","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All investigation is complete. Here is the full review.\n\n---\n\n## Code Review: Monorepo Fix Commit\n\n**Commit:** `2d566ef` -- \"Fix all 6 monorepo breakages from botched merge/refactor\"\n\n**Build:** PASSES (`tsc -b` exits clean)\n**Tests:** ALL 49 PASS across 9 test files, including the structural validation tests for circular dependencies and successful package builds.\n\n---\n\n### Fix 1: Circular Dependency in `/workspace/packages/core/src/types.ts`\n\n**Verdict: Correct.**\n\nThe fix removed the `import { getUserById } from './user.js'` at the top of `types.ts` and deleted the `userExists()` function that depended on it. This cleanly breaks the cycle: `types.ts -> user.ts -> types.ts`.\n\nThe file now contains only pure type/interface declarations with no imports whatsoever, which is exactly what a `types.ts` module should be. The structural test `has no circular dependencies` confirms this passes.\n\nI verified with a global grep that `userExists` is no longer referenced anywhere in the codebase -- no dangling call sites were left behind.\n\n**No issues.**\n\n---\n\n### Fix 2: Half-Renamed `createUser` -> `registerUser` in `/workspace/packages/api/src/routes/users.ts` and `/workspace/packages/worker/src/jobs/sync.ts`\n\n**Verdict: Correct.**\n\nBoth files had their import statements and call sites updated from `createUser` to `registerUser`. The core module (`/workspace/packages/core/src/user.ts` line 34) defines the function as `registerUser`, and the core barrel export (`/workspace/packages/core/src/index.ts` line 10) re-exports it as `registerUser`.\n\nA codebase-wide grep for `createUser` only shows hits in the validation schema name (`createUserSchema`) and its related exports, which are correctly named -- they describe the schema for _creating_ a user, not the function that was renamed.\n\n**No is